---
description: Auto-build Sol Voice Tuner after code changes
alwaysApply: true
globs: ["*.cpp", "*.h", "CMakeLists.txt", "*.cmake"]
---

After any code generation or file changes in the Sol Voice Tuner project:

1. Automatically run the complete build script that handles everything:
   cd <project-root>
   & .\build-and-launch.ps1
   (Do NOT pass -NoLaunch; Ableton must launch on every successful build.)

   This script will:
   - Configure CMake on first run (uses pre-cloned JUCE 8 + Signalsmith Stretch
     in `external/`, falls back to FetchContent if missing)
   - Auto-detect the installed Visual Studio (2026 / 2022 / 2019) via vswhere
   - Incrementally rebuild the Release VST3 (`SolVoiceTuner` target)
   - Copy `Sol Voice Tuner.vst3` into the "63C" subfolder of every
     known VST3 root (Program Files VST3, Ableton User Library VST3, etc.)
   - Remove any stale legacy VST3s from previous builds (e.g. PitchCorrectorVST.vst3)
   - Wait 2 seconds for the filesystem to settle
   - Launch (or focus) Ableton Live
   - Print clear success / error messages at each step

   Useful flags:
     -Clean         : delete build/ first (full rebuild)
     -Reconfigure   : force CMake to re-run even if cache exists
     -NoLaunch      : skip launching Ableton (build + copy only)

   If the build script doesn't exist, fall back to manual commands:
   cd <project-root>
   cmake -S . -B build -G "Visual Studio 18 2026" -A x64
   cmake --build build --config Release --target SolVoiceTuner_VST3
   $shades = "$env:USERPROFILE\Documents\Ableton\User Library\VST3\63C"
   if (-not (Test-Path $shades)) { New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $shades -Force | Out-Null }
   $src = "build\SolVoiceTuner_artefacts\Release\VST3\Sol Voice Tuner.vst3"
   if (Test-Path $src) {
       Copy-Item -Path $src -Destination $shades -Recurse -Force
       Write-Host "Copied Sol Voice Tuner.vst3 -> $shades" -ForegroundColor Green
   }

2. If there are compile errors, diagnose them using the juce-docs MCP tool
   (or web search for Signalsmith Stretch / YIN-related issues), fix the
   code, and retry the build automatically.

3. Brand identity:
   - Company: 63C
   - Plugin colors: cosmic dark navy (#0a0a1f) with bright cyan accents
     (#00d4ff arc, #00b4ff glow). See `Source/SolLookAndFeel.h` for the
     full palette -- match this exactly when adding new UI components.

4. Prioritize real-time-safe audio code (no allocations, locks, or syscalls
   on the audio thread) and modern JUCE 8 idioms (FontOptions, ParameterID
   versionHints, AudioProcessorValueTreeState attachments).
